.TH viper 7 "Viper" "Project overview" "Miscellanea"
.SH NAME
viper \- Overview of the Viper IL toolchain and runtime
.SH DESCRIPTION
Viper is a modular IL and runtime system with:
.IP \(bu 2
An interpreter (VM) with pluggable dispatch strategies.
.IP \(bu 2
Frontends, including a BASIC dialect that lowers to IL.
.IP \(bu 2
Backends for native code emission on supported targets.
.PP
Common user-facing tools:
.TP
\fBviper\fR(1)
Multi-tool driver (run IL, compile BASIC, optimize IL, codegen).
.TP
\fBilrun\fR(1)
Simple IL runner.
.TP
\fBvbasic\fR(1)
BASIC interpreter / IL emitter.
.TP
\fBil-verify\fR(1)
IL verifier.
.TP
\fBbasic-ast-dump\fR(1), \fBbasic-lex-dump\fR(1)
Developer utilities for parsing/lexing BASIC.
.SH FILES
Textual IL files typically end with \fC.il\fR. BASIC sources use \fC.bas\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBviper\fR(1), \fBilrun\fR(1), \fBvbasic\fR(1), \fBil-verify\fR(1)

